TITLE: My First Childhood Divine Experience & An Infinite Journey | P3
VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mxtQGxIxWsc
DATE: March 11, 2026 (recording date); events referenced span entire life journey
LANGUAGE: Hindi (auto-translated)

SUMMARY:
In Part 3, the concluding segment of the series, Maa Noor Ananta brings the narrative full circle and delivers the core spiritual teachings drawn from her life experiences. She begins by acknowledging her two children who are now grown and settled. She reflects on the deeper meaning of life -- that the Paramatma (Supreme Being) does not give birth to anyone without purpose, and those who are sent with a specific purpose will face extraordinary problems in their lives, with every event prompting the question "Why me? Why is this happening to me?" without any apparent reason.

She recaps the key events: the cosmic snake entering her body, the Bhopal and Indira Gandhi incidents, the family's visits to Punjab and Baba Balak Nath temple during annual holidays before permanently relocating in 1991. She emphasizes that post-1991, her story truly began in Punjab with immense ups and downs -- a life whose depth and struggles no one could ever guess from her outward demeanor and lifestyle. The coma incident was the turning point that completely transformed her life -- it generated the deep questioning and awareness that propelled her spiritual journey forward.

She explains that the gold earrings (baliyan) she had offered to Baba Balak Nath as a child remained with her for many years, continually triggering her at various moments. They were finally offered at the Baba Balak Nath shrine much later, after her marriage to Shaili, after having two children, and after a specific life incident -- when the divine timing was right. She explains that the act of offering the earrings upon awakening from the coma, and the final offering years later, were both cosmically timed events.

The most powerful teaching in this part is the distinction between awareness (adhyatm/spirituality) and religious ritual (puja path/dharm). She observes that she has lived among people for 30 years who perform puja-path morning and evening without fail -- they won't drink tea without morning prayer or eat dinner without evening prayer -- yet they live their entire lives "asleep" (spiritually unconscious), unaware of what is happening around them. She declares that puja-path (worship rituals) is NOT the same as awareness. Spirituality (adhyatm) is the inward journey -- going within oneself. Religious ritual is the outward journey. When you truly awaken, even your worship transforms into something entirely different. She calls on viewers to develop awareness because without it, you cannot understand why you meet certain people, why ups and downs come, or what your true purpose is.

She concludes by expressing her intention to share more experiences in future videos, including her spiritual travels (yatras), the kriyas (cosmic processes) she has undergone at various sacred places, and how divine messages come to her. She affirms that life is beautiful and should be lived with love and awareness.

KEY REVELATIONS:
- Those sent to Earth with a divine purpose will face extraordinary, unexplainable problems -- this is how the Paramatma triggers awakening
- The coma was the ultimate turning point: it generated the deep inner questioning ("Who am I?") that launched her conscious spiritual journey
- The gold earrings (baliyan) served as a decades-long spiritual trigger -- a physical object carrying cosmic significance across years until the right moment for final offering at Baba Balak Nath
- Critical distinction: Puja-path (religious rituals) is the OUTWARD journey; Adhyatm (spirituality) is the INWARD journey -- they are fundamentally different
- People who worship ritualistically for decades can remain spiritually asleep -- ritual alone does not produce awakening
- She has lived among such ritualistic-yet-unaware people for 30 years, providing direct observational evidence
- True awakening transforms how you worship -- it becomes a completely different experience
- The question "Who am I?" (Hu am I?) is the essential catalyst for spiritual awakening -- until this question arises within, one cannot grasp life's purpose
- She has no medical dependencies, no concept of depression, no need for painkillers -- self-healing through awareness
- Planetary energies and birth chart influence daily life events; awareness of these cycles deepens understanding
- Life purpose became clear in 2010; she intends to share more about her yatras and kriyas at sacred sites

TIMELINE EVENTS:
- 1971: Born in Namrup, Assam
- 1984: Cosmic snake event; kundalini activation (Part 1)
- 1984: Bhopal Gas Tragedy and Indira Gandhi assassination draw her attention (Part 1)
- ~1986-1987: Unexplained coma; healed by kirtan; gold earrings offered to Baba Balak Nath (Part 2)
- Annual holidays: Family visited Punjab and Baba Balak Nath temple every year from Assam
- 1991: Permanent shift from Assam to Punjab
- 1992 onward: Met Shaili; karmic life began; had two children
- ~2004: Brief modeling exploration; telefilm in Jammu with snake-related character
- 2008: Full surrender and clarity on spiritual path
- 2010: Life purpose fully understood
- Post-marriage specific incident: Gold earrings finally offered at Baba Balak Nath shrine (exact date not given)
- March 11, 2026: Three-part video series recorded

ORIGINAL HINDI KEY QUOTES:
- "जिसको एक पर्पस देकर इस धरती पर भेजा है ना उसके लाइफ में बहुत सारी प्रॉब्लम्स होगी, विदाउट एनी रीज़न" = "The one who is sent to this Earth with a purpose will have many problems in their life, without any reason"
- "वो जो कोमा में जाना मेरी लाइफ को बिल्कुल बदल देता है" = "That going into a coma completely changed my life"
- "अध्यात्म अलग चीज है, अध्यात्म खुद के अंदर जाना, खुद के अंदर की यात्रा" = "Spirituality is a different thing -- spirituality is going within yourself, an inward journey"
- "पूजा पाठ बाहर की यात्रा... जब आप अंदर जाग जाओगे ना तो आप पूजा पाठ का मतलब भी समझ जाओगे" = "Worship rituals are the outward journey... when you awaken within, you will understand the true meaning of worship"
- "जब तक आपके अंदर यह सवाल नहीं आएगा, हु एम आई? तब तक आप अपनी लाइफ को नहीं समझ पाओगे" = "Until this question arises within you -- Who am I? -- you will not be able to understand your life"
- "हर एक घटना ने मुझे सिखाया, मैं जो कुछ भी हूं ना अपनी लाइफ डे टू डे लाइफ के इवेंट से हूं" = "Every event taught me; whatever I am is from the day-to-day events of my own life"
- "मैं ऐसे लोगों के बीच में रहती हूं पिछले 30 साल से... सुबह मतलब पूजा पाठ किए बिना चाय नहीं पिएंगे... लेकिन सोकर जीवन बिता रहे हैं" = "I have lived among such people for 30 years... they won't drink tea without morning puja... but they are living their lives asleep"
- "जिंदगी बहुत खूबसूरत है, इसको बड़े प्यार से जिए, एंजॉय करो इसको" = "Life is very beautiful, live it with great love, enjoy it"

YUG PARIVARTAN ASPECT: This concluding part delivers the foundational teaching of Yug Parivartan: the transition from Kaliyuga to Satyuga is fundamentally about a shift from external ritualism to inner awakening. The 30 years of living among ritualistically devout yet spiritually unconscious people serves as a direct commentary on the Kaliyuga condition -- where the form of religion persists but its essence is lost. Yug Parivartan demands a mass awakening where humanity moves from "soke jeena" (living asleep) to "jagrut hoke jeena" (living awakened). The entire three-part narrative -- from the cosmic snake of 1984 to the present -- maps the journey of a Yug Parivartan soul: initial activation, purification through suffering, karmic relocation, self-realization, and finally the mission to awaken others. The emphasis on awareness (jagruti/awareness) as the supreme necessity echoes the core Yug Parivartan message that the new age will be defined not by new rituals but by awakened consciousness.


